definition.value: This is an AE which is an injury to part of the musculoskeletal or nervous system caused by repetitive use, vibrations, compression or long periods in a fixed position.
This is an AE which is injury on a structural frame that supports an animal body.
This is an AE which is damage to the spinal cord that causes temporary or permanent changes in its function.
This is an AE which is injuries that occur during sport, athletic activities, or exercising.
This is an AE which is injury on  a tough, high-tensile-strength band of dense fibrous connective tissue that connects muscle to bone.
This is an AE which is injury on a  muscular organ in the mouth of a typical vertebrate.
This is an AE which refers to trauma (injury) to the teeth and/or periodontium (gums, periodontal ligament, alveolar bone), and nearby soft tissues such as the lips, tongue, etc.

This is an AE which is a non-medical term describing a range of injuries to the neck caused by or related to a sudden distortion of the neck associated with extension, although the exact injury mechanisms remain unknown.
This is an AE which occurs when living tissue is exposed to a corrosive substance (such as a strong acid, base or oxidizer) or a cytotoxic agent (such as mustard gas, lewisite or arsine).

This is an AE which refers macrophages present dysfunctional efferocytosis and abnormal phenotypes, which could result in excessive neutrophil accumulation and prolonged inflammation, thereby eventually hindering wound repair.

This is an AE which is part of the complex biological response of wound tissues to harmful stimuli, such as pathogens, damaged cells, or irritants, and is a protective response involving immune cells, blood vessels, and molecular mediators.
This is an AE which is a type of injury which happens relatively quickly in which skin is torn, cut, or punctured (an open wound).
This is an AE which is those wounds acquired during surgical procedures.

This is an AE which refers associating anterograde amnesia persisting for fifteen years, with temporal disorientation, false recognitions, initially intense transitory confabulation and secondarily bursts of confabulation, intact remote memory and persistence of old learnings.
This is an AE which is a form of acquired epilepsy that results from brain damage caused by physical trauma to the brain (traumatic brain injury, abbreviated TBI).
This is an AE which is a rare disorder occured on post-traumatic that is associated with neck pain and tingling/numbness of the tongue.
This is an AE which is a distressing feeling on the post-traumatic often caused by intense or damaging stimuli.

This is an AE which is a mental and behavioral disorder that can develop because of exposure to a traumatic event, such as sexual assault, warfare, traffic collisions, child abuse, domestic violence or other threats on a person's life.
This is an AE which is a type of injury which happens relatively quickly in which skin is torn, cut, where blunt force trauma causes a contusion (a closed wound).
This is an AE which usually resulting from accidental injury; there are pathogenic organisms and foreign bodies in the wound.

This is an AE which is a localized wound  bleeding outside of blood vessels, due to either disease or trauma including injury or surgery and may involve blood continuing to seep from broken capillaries.
This is an AE which is blood escaping from the circulatory system from damaged  wound haemorrhage blood vessels.
This is an AE which is a form of cell injury which results in the premature death of cells in living tissue by autolysis occured on the wound.

This is an AE which is a type of application site injury which happens relatively quickly in which skin is torn, cut, or punctured (an open wound), or where blunt force trauma causes a contusion (a closed wound) .

This is an AE which is a small pocket of body fluid (lymph, serum, plasma, blood, or pus) within the upper layers of the skin, usually caused by forceful rubbing (friction), burning, freezing, chemical exposure or infection and is rupture.
This is an AE which is a closed sac, having a distinct envelope and division compared with the nearby tissue and is rupture.
This is an AE which is a rare injury that occurs primarily during strength training.
This is an AE which is breakage of the amniotic sac before the onset of labor.
This is an AE which is a common complication of chronic knee arthritis.
This is an AE which is a type of abnormal and excessive growth of tissue and is rupture.
This is an AE which is a specific form of penetrating trauma to the skin that results from a knife or a similar pointed object.
This is an AE which is a wound, usually a puncture or laceration, caused by the teeth.

This is an AE which is a skin injury that occurs when exposed to extreme low temperatures, causing the freezing of the skin or other tissues, commonly affecting the fingers, toes, nose, ears, cheeks and chin areas.

This is an AE which is a medical condition in which damage occurs to capillary beds in the skin, most often in the hands or feet, when blood perfuses into the nearby tissue resulting in redness, itching, inflammation, and possibly blisters.
This is an AE which is substances that can cause death, injury or harm to organs, tissues, cells, and DNA usually by chemical reactions , when an organism is exposed to a sufficient quantity.
This is an AE which is a mark of abrasion on a surface.

This is an AE which is a slough or piece of dead tissue that is cast off from the surface of the skin, particularly after a burn injury, but also seen in gangrene, ulcer, fungal infections, necrotizing spider bite wounds, tick bites associated with spotted fevers and exposure to cutaneous anthrax.
This is an AE which is the toxic effect of certain metals in certain forms and doses on life.
This is an AE which is the negative behavior and physical effects caused by a recent consumption of alcohol.
This is an AE which refers irregular tear-like wounds caused by some blunt trauma.
This is an AE which is physical damage to body tissues caused by a difference in pressure between a gas space inside, or in contact with, the body, and the surrounding gas or fluid.
This is an AE which is a sensation that causes the desire or reflex to scratch scar.
This is an AE which prior to lenvatinib administration prevented hyperammonemia and hepatic encephalopathy.

This is an AE which is a type of hematoma of administration site tissue, the most common cause being capillaries damaged by trauma, causing localized bleeding that extravasates into the surrounding interstitial tissues.
This is an AE which is a bacterial infection involving the inner layers of the administration site skin.
This is an AE which is redness of the administration site skin or mucous membranes, caused by hyperemia (increased blood flow) in superficial capillaries.

This is an AE which is a localized bleeding such as administration site outside of blood vessels, due to either disease or trauma including injury or surgery and may involve blood continuing to seep from broken capillaries.
This is an AE which is blood escaping from the circulatory system from damaged blood vessels on the administration site.

This is an AE which is a common side effect of various medical conditions which manifests as a reduced sense of touch or sensation, or a partial loss of sensitivity to sensory stimuli on the administration site.
This is an AE which is dermal thickening on the administration site causing the cutaneous surface to feel thicker and firmer.
